{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# RC2b: snapshot-horizon-safe replay (no silent sub-horizon drop)\n\n## Why\nWhen two clones write at once, one can compact and delete the events it folded before seeing the other's\nevent. After merge, that event sorts BEFORE the snapshot and replay's positional skip drops it regardless of\n`source_event_uuids` -> silent data loss. Live store holds ~11 such orphans.\n\n## Decision (ACCEPTED): Option 1 (rebuild-on-stray) + Option 3 (conservative horizon)\nOption 2 (per-field LWW-by-timestamp) deferred as a possible follow-up.\n\n## Concrete rules (all symbols/units resolved)\n- SETTLED (Option 3): compaction folds an event only if `hlc.physical_now() - event_ts >= COMPACTION_HORIZON_NS`.\n  `COMPACTION_HORIZON_NS` is a NEW config value on `CompactConfig` in `_config_schema.py`, default\n  `1_800_000_000_000` (= 1800 s expressed in HLC NANOSECOND ticks â€” HLC uses `time.time_ns()`, so the horizon\n  must be nanoseconds, not the integer 1800). Younger \"hot-edge\" events stay live `.json` for the next cycle.\n  (The earlier \"clone completed >=1 git fetch this pass\" clause is DROPPED: `ensure_fresh`/`reconverge` return\n  None unconditionally and expose no success signal â€” the time-based horizon alone is sufficient and verifiable.)\n- REBUILD (Option 1): fsck detects a merged-in pre-snapshot orphan (KNOWN-type `.json` sorting before the\n  SNAPSHOT, uuid absent from `source_event_uuids`) and rebuilds that ticket's snapshot from the full ordered log\n  INCLUDING `.retired`. This requires a NEW `include_retired: bool = False` parameter on `reduce_ticket`\n  (`reducer/_api.py`) AND on `prepare_event_files` (`reducer/_cache.py`, both listing paths at ~line 97 and ~line\n  102) â€” neither exists today; adding it is in-scope here (callers: this rebuild + A3). Rebuild writes `<snap>.tmp`\n  + atomic `os.rename`; the old snapshot is moved to `<snap>.bak` by the rebuild process and deleted by that same\n  process after a clean replay round-trip in the same run. Idempotent + resumable; log (WARN) each detected orphan\n  + each rebuild and increment a rebuild counter. Concurrency: rebuild only when quiesced OR re-check the event log\n  after rebuild and redo if a new event landed.\n\n## Dependencies (explicit)\n- A1 = tricolour-head-ratfish delivers the `.retired` rename + `RETIRED_SUFFIX`/`is_active_event` (depends_on, wired).\n- A3 = entitled-unsweet-nutria REUSES the `include_retired` rebuild path authored here.\n\n## Scope (enumerated edit targets)\n`reducer/_processors.py` (process_snapshot + positional skip ~648-702), `reducer/_api.py` (`include_retired`),\n`reducer/_cache.py` (`prepare_event_files` both listing paths), `_commands/fsck.py` (orphan-detect + rebuild\ntrigger), `_commands/compact.py` (conservative-horizon fold guard), `_config_schema.py` (`CompactConfig.COMPACTION_HORIZON_NS`).\n`reducer/_sort.py` is READ-ONLY context (no change). NOT the reconciler code.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `COMPACTION_HORIZON_NS` added to `CompactConfig` (default 1_800_000_000_000 ns), documented as 1800 s in HLC ticks; ADR records the rule.\n- [ ] Unit test: an event younger than the horizon (`physical_now()-event_ts < COMPACTION_HORIZON_NS`) is NOT folded.\n- [ ] `reduce_ticket`/`prepare_event_files` gain `include_retired`; default False preserves current behavior; True includes `*.retired` in replay.\n- [ ] fsck detects a pre-snapshot orphan and rebuilds the snapshot (atomic tmp+rename; `.bak` deleted only after a clean round-trip in the same run; rebuild counter incremented; WARN logged).\n- [ ] A merged-in pre-horizon orphan is no longer silently dropped. Two-clone sub-horizon-append regression test: RED before, GREEN after.\n- [ ] Determinism proof: `reduce_ticket` run twice on the same file set (incl. shuffled `os.listdir` order) returns equal compiled_state. Proof: `python -m pytest tests/scripts/reducer/ -k determinism -q`.\n- [ ] Decision + design recorded in an ADR.\n\n\n## Round-4 refinements (from plan review)\n- CACHE: `compute_dir_hash`/`prepare_event_files` (_cache.py) hash `*.json` filenames only. With\n  `include_retired=True`, EITHER extend `compute_dir_hash` to include `.retired` metadata OR bypass the cache for\n  the rebuild path â€” otherwise a stale cache hit ignores retired files. `scan_for_latest_snapshot` must also see\n  the same file set. (AC: a test asserts the rebuild path does not return a stale cached state.)\n- CONFIG: add a `COMPACTION_HORIZON_NS` env-var alias in `config.py` (the established alias-registry pattern), not\n  just `CompactConfig`.\n- DEPENDENCY: A1 (tricolour-head-ratfish) ADDS `RETIRED_SUFFIX`/`is_active_event`/`.retired` (they are NOT in the\n  codebase today); this ticket depends on A1 landing first.\n- `.bak` CRASH RECOVERY: if `<snap>.bak` exists at rebuild start, a prior rebuild was interrupted â€” restore from\n  `.bak` (or re-rebuild) before proceeding; `.bak` is deleted only after a clean replay round-trip in the same run.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783478497534602001,"uuid":"3a743cd8-436a-43e1-a992-854c71e1962e"}